    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a really solid start. it definitely hits the moral angle hard. can you expand on that a bit more? specifically, can you help me write a section that breaks down why the \"meritocracy\" argument—the idea that people just get what they deserve based on hard work—is actually a flawed or even harmful way to look at this issue? i want to show that it's basically just a way to ignore the systemic stuff.",
