    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"meritocracy\" myth is a dangerous fiction used to mask entrenched racial bias. It falsely implies that success is purely an individual outcome, completely ignoring the structural barriers like discriminatory housing policies and unequal educational funding that disproportionately affect people of color. By claiming success is solely earned, this ideology absolves society of its responsibility to correct inherited disadvantages. True meritocracy cannot exist when the starting line is fundamentally different for every racial group.",
      "source": "target",
